- Honoured the hosts request to let her know when I was going to used the bathroom for more than 20 minutes 
- Was kind and patient with her dog
- Was respectful of her home and space 
- Took our the trash and left the room neat
- Said good morning and hello when I came back to the room
- Communicated at the beginning of the stay that I felt exhausted and stayed quietly resting in my room as a result, on Sunday, and most of my 2 day stay. 

It was a hostile atmosphere and on a few occasions the host glared at me when I was going about my business, without saying anything to me. I felt violated and confused- and actually afraid to speak up. As I was walking out the door to check out the host aggressively expressed how unhappy she was with me, told me I was bad at communicating and thought I had been very rude. I was extremely confused, hurt and shaking as I left the house. 
I’m generally empathic and patient, but as an Airbnb host there are responsibilities such as respecting someone’s needs and space and not projecting expectations onto guests in a way that feels threatening. I don’t feel this host meets these responsibilities. Perhaps this more so with, as mentioned, sensitive introverts - such as myself. I did communicate clearly I was tired - I take responsibility however, for not clearly communicating I didn’t want to have small talk or lengthy conversations, which I understand for some people - if not spoken about - can come across as rude. I did not intend to be rude AT ALL. 
I have 60+ good reviews because I AM a respectful and honest guest. 
If you’re just travelling through Sydney and looking to explore the city, are more extroverted and up for small talk or casual chatting, plus feel prepared to closely communicate with a host about your comings and goings, then this place would be fit for you.

33476227:
The location is what makes this place. Very convenient for the city and Newtown areas, or even getting around with central station and Broadway so close that it is easy to catch a cab or similar. It was very easy to access and had good information for tourists. 

The accommodation is basic and meets all the requirements of what accommodation should be. We are staying for 5 nights and we ran out of toilet paper however! Tissues saved the day.

I am not a neat freak but this accommodation was one of the more unclean ones I have stayed in. More than a generic vacuum or mop could fix. The bathroom had mould throughout it, and the skirting boards were thickly coated in dust. The walls were patched up pretty roughly and you could tell some water damage has previously occurred, but it is an older place so it is never going to be perfect! 

Other than the mould, the rest didn’t bother my husband or I but I know friends and family of mine wouldn’t be impressed. 

The apartment came with tea and coffee facilities also (pods, tea, milk etc), but my husband said the milk frother smelt like mouldy milk so it didn’t get used. It also came with great kitchen facilities such as crockery and appliances. 

The bed was very comfortable and soft, came with good linen etc. 
Again, a couple of stains on white linen but didn’t bother us much since it was on the doona cover and not the sheets or pillows. It really needs a fitted sheet and not a top sheet just tucked into the mattress. The fitted sheet kept on pulling out and we woke up to find ourselves sleeping directly on the mattress (no mattress protector etc). 

Overall, it’s budget accommodation in an old city like Sydney. We booked it for the location and were not in the apartment most of the time. If the apartment was cleaner and had a fitted sheet/mattress protectors etc I would recommend this apartment to others!
